Doxygen

In your career you will be asked to document everything you do.

Many programmers will shun away from doing such activities. It is our goal that this will not be you. This document was generated using the open source tool Doxygen which shows how documentation can be automatically pulled from inline comments to produce a clean document. We encourage you to add to the documentation we have given as you work on the machine problem. These comments will NOT be graded.

For more information on how to use Doxygen see the manual listed below. Running 'make' will create your own web document stored in 'doc/html'.
